  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IT Project Manager (Infra / Apps)",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Oversee end-to-end IT and engineering project delivery, ensuring projects are completed on time, within scope and budget.</li><li>Manage full project lifecycle including requirements gathering, design, development, integration, testing, commissioning, and maintenance.</li><li>Develop and communicate project plans, defining roles, objectives, deliverables, schedules, critical paths, and risks to teams and customers.</li><li>Monitor and control project budgets, costs, and resource allocation to maximize revenue and margin.</li><li>Establish risk management plans and implement mitigation strategies.</li><li>Manage project changes with impact analysis, resolution, and contingency planning.</li><li>Lead and mentor high-performance project teams, fostering collaboration and accountability.</li><li>Maintain proactive relationships with stakeholders, providing regular progress updates and managing escalations.</li><li>Support pre-sales activities, including developing Requests for Proposals (RFPs) with solution teams.</li></ul><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in IT, Computer Science, Engineering, or equivalent.</li><li>5+ years’ experience managing large-scale IT and engineering integration projects with cross-functional teams.</li><li>Knowledge of government security standards is a plus.</li><li>Professional certifications (e.g., PMP, CITPM, CISSP) preferred.</li><li>Experience in turnkey development, implementation, and maintenance of large-scale, multi-platform, multi-vendor IT and engineering systems.</li><li>Proven success managing multi-million-dollar projects in government or commercial sectors.</li><li>Strong skills in project management, service delivery, client relations, planning, scheduling, budgeting, financial management, quality assurance, and negotiation.</li><li>Demonstrated leadership in staff management, motivation, performance appraisal, and professional development.</li><li>Hands-on, proactive, and customer-focused with excellent communication, presentation, and interpersonal skills.</li></ul><p><p><strong>Work Location: </strong>Tampines<br /></p><p>(EA Reg No: 20C0312)<br />Please email a copy of your detailed resume to <strong>qianyu@talentsis.com.sg</strong> for immediate processing.<br />Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p></p>",
